395
401inline bool isInvalidData(double value) { return qIsNaN(value) || qIsInf(value); }
402
408inline bool isInvalidData(double value1, double value2) {
409 return isInvalidData(value1) || isInvalidData(value2);
410}
411
418inline void setMarginValue(QMargins &margins, QCP::MarginSide side, int value) {
419 switch (side) {
420 case QCP::msLeft:
421 margins.setLeft(value);
422 break;
423 case QCP::msRight:
424 margins.setRight(value);
425 break;
426 case QCP::msTop:
427 margins.setTop(value);
428 break;
429 case QCP::msBottom:
430 margins.setBottom(value);
431 break;
432 case QCP::msAll:
433 margins = QMargins(value, value, value, value);
434 break;
435 default:
436 break;
437 }
438}
439
447inline int getMarginValue(const QMargins &margins, QCP::MarginSide side) {
448 switch (side) {
449 case QCP::msLeft:
450 return margins.left();
451 case QCP::msRight:
452 return margins.right();
453 case QCP::msTop:
454 return margins.top();
455 case QCP::msBottom:
456 return margins.bottom();
457 default:
458 break;
459 }
460 return 0;
461}

475class QCP_LIB_DECL QCPVector2D {
476 public:
477 QCPVector2D();
478 QCPVector2D(double x, double y);
479 QCPVector2D(const QPoint &point);
480 QCPVector2D(const QPointF &point);
481
482 // getters:
483 double x() const { return mX; }
484 double y() const { return mY; }
485 double &rx() { return mX; }
486 double &ry() { return mY; }
487
488 // setters:
489 void setX(double x) { mX = x; }
490 void setY(double y) { mY = y; }
491
492 // non-virtual methods:
493 double length() const { return qSqrt(mX * mX + mY * mY); }
494 double lengthSquared() const { return mX * mX + mY * mY; }
495 double angle() const { return qAtan2(mY, mX); }
496 QPoint toPoint() const { return QPoint(int(mX), int(mY)); }
497 QPointF toPointF() const { return QPointF(mX, mY); }
498
499 bool isNull() const { return qIsNull(mX) && qIsNull(mY); }
500 void normalize();
501 QCPVector2D normalized() const;
502 QCPVector2D perpendicular() const { return QCPVector2D(-mY, mX); }
503 double dot(const QCPVector2D &vec) const { return mX * vec.mX + mY * vec.mY; }
504 double distanceSquaredToLine(const QCPVector2D &start, const QCPVector2D &end) const;
505 double distanceSquaredToLine(const QLineF &line) const;
506 double distanceToStraightLine(const QCPVector2D &base, const QCPVector2D &direction) const;
507
508 QCPVector2D &operator*=(double factor);
509 QCPVector2D &operator/=(double divisor);
510 QCPVector2D &operator+=(const QCPVector2D &vector);
511 QCPVector2D &operator-=(const QCPVector2D &vector);
512
513 private:
514 // property members:
515 double mX, mY;
516
517 friend inline const QCPVector2D operator*(double factor, const QCPVector2D &vec);
518 friend inline const QCPVector2D operator*(const QCPVector2D &vec, double factor);
519 friend inline const QCPVector2D operator/(const QCPVector2D &vec, double divisor);
520 friend inline const QCPVector2D operator+(const QCPVector2D &vec1, const QCPVector2D &vec2);
521 friend inline const QCPVector2D operator-(const QCPVector2D &vec1, const QCPVector2D &vec2);
522 friend inline const QCPVector2D operator-(const QCPVector2D &vec);
523};
524Q_DECLARE_TYPEINFO(QCPVector2D, Q_MOVABLE_TYPE);
525
526inline const QCPVector2D operator*(double factor, const QCPVector2D &vec) {
527 return QCPVector2D(vec.mX * factor, vec.mY * factor);
528}
529inline const QCPVector2D operator*(const QCPVector2D &vec, double factor) {
530 return QCPVector2D(vec.mX * factor, vec.mY * factor);
531}
532inline const QCPVector2D operator/(const QCPVector2D &vec, double divisor) {
533 return QCPVector2D(vec.mX / divisor, vec.mY / divisor);
534}
535inline const QCPVector2D operator+(const QCPVector2D &vec1, const QCPVector2D &vec2) {
536 return QCPVector2D(vec1.mX + vec2.mX, vec1.mY + vec2.mY);
537}
538inline const QCPVector2D operator-(const QCPVector2D &vec1, const QCPVector2D &vec2) {
539 return QCPVector2D(vec1.mX - vec2.mX, vec1.mY - vec2.mY);
540}
541inline const QCPVector2D operator-(const QCPVector2D &vec) { return QCPVector2D(-vec.mX, -vec.mY); }
542
547inline QDebug operator<<(QDebug d, const QCPVector2D &vec) {
548 d.nospace() << "QCPVector2D(" << vec.x() << ", " << vec.y() << ")";
549 return d.space();
550}

882 bool operator==(const QCPRange &other) const { return lower == other.lower && upper == other.upper; }
883 bool operator!=(const QCPRange &other) const { return !(*this == other); }
884
885 QCPRange &operator+=(const double &value) {
886 lower += value;
887 upper += value;
888 return *this;
889 }
890 QCPRange &operator-=(const double &value) {
891 lower -= value;
892 upper -= value;
893 return *this;
894 }
895 QCPRange &operator*=(const double &value) {
896 lower *= value;
897 upper *= value;
898 return *this;
899 }
900 QCPRange &operator/=(const double &value) {
901 lower /= value;
902 upper /= value;
903 return *this;
904 }
905 friend inline const QCPRange operator+(const QCPRange &, double);
906 friend inline const QCPRange operator+(double, const QCPRange &);
907 friend inline const QCPRange operator-(const QCPRange &range, double value);
908 friend inline const QCPRange operator*(const QCPRange &range, double value);
909 friend inline const QCPRange operator*(double value, const QCPRange &range);
910 friend inline const QCPRange operator/(const QCPRange &range, double value);
911
912 double size() const { return upper - lower; }
913 double center() const { return (upper + lower) * 0.5; }
914 void normalize() {
915 if (lower > upper) qSwap(lower, upper);
916 }
917 void expand(const QCPRange &otherRange);
918 void expand(double includeCoord);
919 QCPRange expanded(const QCPRange &otherRange) const;
920 QCPRange expanded(double includeCoord) const;
921 QCPRange bounded(double lowerBound, double upperBound) const;
922 QCPRange sanitizedForLogScale() const;
923 QCPRange sanitizedForLinScale() const;
924 bool contains(double value) const { return value >= lower && value <= upper; }
925
926 static bool validRange(double lower, double upper);
927 static bool validRange(const QCPRange &range);
928 static const double minRange;
929 static const double maxRange;
930};

2724template <class DataType>
2725inline bool qcpLessThanSortKey(const DataType &a, const DataType &b) {
2726 return a.sortKey() < b.sortKey();
2727}

2934template <class DataType>

2951 add(data);

2963template <class DataType>
2964void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::set(const QVector<DataType> &data, bool alreadySorted) {
2965 mData = data;
2966 mPreallocSize = 0;
2967 mPreallocIteration = 0;
2968 if (!alreadySorted) sort();
2969}
2970
2977template <class DataType>
2978void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::add(const QCPDataContainer<DataType> &data) {
2979 if (data.isEmpty()) return;
2980
2981 const int n = data.size();
2982 const int oldSize = size();
2983
2984 if (oldSize > 0 &&
2985 !qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>(
2986 *constBegin(), *(data.constEnd() -
2987 1))) // prepend if new data keys are all smaller than or equal to existing ones
2988 {
2989 if (mPreallocSize < n) preallocateGrow(n);
2990 mPreallocSize -= n;
2991 std::copy(data.constBegin(), data.constEnd(), begin());
2992 } else // don't need to prepend, so append and merge if necessary
2993 {
2994 mData.resize(mData.size() + n);
2995 std::copy(data.constBegin(), data.constEnd(), end() - n);
2996 if (oldSize > 0 &&
2997 !qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>(
2998 *(constEnd() - n - 1), *(constEnd() - n))) // if appended range keys aren't all greater than
2999 // existing ones, merge the two partitions
3000 std::inplace_merge(begin(), end() - n, end(), qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3001 }
3002}
3003
3012template <class DataType>
3013void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::add(const QVector<DataType> &data, bool alreadySorted) {
3014 if (data.isEmpty()) return;
3015 if (isEmpty()) {
3016 set(data, alreadySorted);
3017 return;
3018 }
3019
3020 const int n = data.size();
3021 const int oldSize = size();
3022
3023 if (alreadySorted && oldSize > 0 &&
3024 !qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>(
3025 *constBegin(),
3026 *(data.constEnd() -
3027 1))) // prepend if new data is sorted and keys are all smaller than or equal to existing ones
3028 {
3029 if (mPreallocSize < n) preallocateGrow(n);
3030 mPreallocSize -= n;
3031 std::copy(data.constBegin(), data.constEnd(), begin());
3032 } else // don't need to prepend, so append and then sort and merge if necessary
3033 {
3034 mData.resize(mData.size() + n);
3035 std::copy(data.constBegin(), data.constEnd(), end() - n);
3036 if (!alreadySorted) // sort appended subrange if it wasn't already sorted
3037 std::sort(end() - n, end(), qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3038 if (oldSize > 0 &&
3039 !qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>(
3040 *(constEnd() - n - 1), *(constEnd() - n))) // if appended range keys aren't all greater than
3041 // existing ones, merge the two partitions
3042 std::inplace_merge(begin(), end() - n, end(), qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3043 }
3044}
3045
3052template <class DataType>
3053void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::add(const DataType &data) {
3054 if (isEmpty() ||
3055 !qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>(
3056 data, *(constEnd() -
3057 1))) // quickly handle appends if new data key is greater or equal to existing ones
3058 {
3059 mData.append(data);
3060 } else if (qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>(
3061 data, *constBegin())) // quickly handle prepends using preallocated space
3062 {
3063 if (mPreallocSize < 1) preallocateGrow(1);
3064 --mPreallocSize;
3065 *begin() = data;
3066 } else // handle inserts, maintaining sorted keys
3067 {
3068 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::iterator insertionPoint =
3069 std::lower_bound(begin(), end(), data, qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3070 mData.insert(insertionPoint, data);
3071 }
3072}
3073
3079template <class DataType>
3080void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::removeBefore(double sortKey) {
3081 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::iterator it = begin();
3082 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::iterator itEnd =
3083 std::lower_bound(begin(), end(), DataType::fromSortKey(sortKey), qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3084 mPreallocSize += int(itEnd - it); // don't actually delete, just add it to the preallocated block (if it
3085 // gets too large, squeeze will take care of it)
3086 if (mAutoSqueeze) performAutoSqueeze();
3087}
3088
3094template <class DataType>
3095void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::removeAfter(double sortKey) {
3096 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::iterator it =
3097 std::upper_bound(begin(), end(), DataType::fromSortKey(sortKey), qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3098 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::iterator itEnd = end();
3099 mData.erase(it, itEnd); // typically adds it to the postallocated block
3100 if (mAutoSqueeze) performAutoSqueeze();
3101}
3102
3110template <class DataType>
3111void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::remove(double sortKeyFrom, double sortKeyTo) {
3112 if (sortKeyFrom >= sortKeyTo || isEmpty()) return;
3113
3114 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::iterator it =
3115 std::lower_bound(begin(), end(), DataType::fromSortKey(sortKeyFrom), qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3116 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::iterator itEnd =
3117 std::upper_bound(it, end(), DataType::fromSortKey(sortKeyTo), qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3118 mData.erase(it, itEnd);
3119 if (mAutoSqueeze) performAutoSqueeze();
3120}
3121
3131template <class DataType>
3132void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::remove(double sortKey) {
3133 QCPDataContainer::iterator it =
3134 std::lower_bound(begin(), end(), DataType::fromSortKey(sortKey), qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3135 if (it != end() && it->sortKey() == sortKey) {
3136 if (it == begin())
3137 ++mPreallocSize; // don't actually delete, just add it to the preallocated block (if it gets too
3138 // large, squeeze will take care of it)
3139 else
3140 mData.erase(it);
3141 }
3142 if (mAutoSqueeze) performAutoSqueeze();
3143}
3144
3150template <class DataType>
3151void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::clear() {
3152 mData.clear();
3153 mPreallocIteration = 0;
3154 mPreallocSize = 0;
3155}
3156
3168template <class DataType>
3169void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::sort() {
3170 std::sort(begin(), end(), qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3171}
3172
3183template <class DataType>
3184void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::squeeze(bool preAllocation, bool postAllocation) {
3185 if (preAllocation) {
3186 if (mPreallocSize > 0) {
3187 std::copy(begin(), end(), mData.begin());
3188 mData.resize(size());
3189 mPreallocSize = 0;
3190 }
3191 mPreallocIteration = 0;
3192 }
3193 if (postAllocation) mData.squeeze();
3194}
3195
3211template <class DataType>
3212typename QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator QCPDataContainer<DataType>::findBegin(
3213 double sortKey, bool expandedRange) const {
3214 if (isEmpty()) return constEnd();
3215
3216 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator it = std::lower_bound(
3217 constBegin(), constEnd(), DataType::fromSortKey(sortKey), qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3218 if (expandedRange && it != constBegin()) // also covers it == constEnd case, and we know --constEnd is
3219 // valid because mData isn't empty
3220 --it;
3221 return it;
3222}
3223
3239template <class DataType>
3240typename QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator QCPDataContainer<DataType>::findEnd(
3241 double sortKey, bool expandedRange) const {
3242 if (isEmpty()) return constEnd();
3243
3244 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator it = std::upper_bound(
3245 constBegin(), constEnd(), DataType::fromSortKey(sortKey), qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3246 if (expandedRange && it != constEnd()) ++it;
3247 return it;
3248}
3249
3265template <class DataType>
3266QCPRange QCPDataContainer<DataType>::keyRange(bool &foundRange, QCP::SignDomain signDomain) {
3267 if (isEmpty()) {
3268 foundRange = false;
3269 return QCPRange();
3270 }
3271 QCPRange range;
3272 bool haveLower = false;
3273 bool haveUpper = false;
3274 double current;
3275
3276 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator it = constBegin();
3277 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator itEnd = constEnd();
3278 if (signDomain == QCP::sdBoth) // range may be anywhere
3279 {
3280 if (DataType::sortKeyIsMainKey()) // if DataType is sorted by main key (e.g. QCPGraph, but not
3281 // QCPCurve), use faster algorithm by finding just first and last
3282 // key with non-NaN value
3283 {
3284 while (it != itEnd) // find first non-nan going up from left
3285 {
3286 if (!qIsNaN(it->mainValue())) {
3287 range.lower = it->mainKey();
3288 haveLower = true;
3289 break;
3290 }
3291 ++it;
3292 }
3293 it = itEnd;
3294 while (it != constBegin()) // find first non-nan going down from right
3295 {
3296 --it;
3297 if (!qIsNaN(it->mainValue())) {
3298 range.upper = it->mainKey();
3299 haveUpper = true;
3300 break;
3301 }
3302 }
3303 } else // DataType is not sorted by main key, go through all data points and accordingly expand
3304 // range
3305 {
3306 while (it != itEnd) {
3307 if (!qIsNaN(it->mainValue())) {
3308 current = it->mainKey();
3309 if (current < range.lower || !haveLower) {
3310 range.lower = current;
3311 haveLower = true;
3312 }
3313 if (current > range.upper || !haveUpper) {
3314 range.upper = current;
3315 haveUpper = true;
3316 }
3317 }
3318 ++it;
3319 }
3320 }
3321 } else if (signDomain == QCP::sdNegative) // range may only be in the negative sign domain
3322 {
3323 while (it != itEnd) {
3324 if (!qIsNaN(it->mainValue())) {
3325 current = it->mainKey();
3326 if ((current < range.lower || !haveLower) && current < 0) {
3327 range.lower = current;
3328 haveLower = true;
3329 }
3330 if ((current > range.upper || !haveUpper) && current < 0) {
3331 range.upper = current;
3332 haveUpper = true;
3333 }
3334 }
3335 ++it;
3336 }
3337 } else if (signDomain == QCP::sdPositive) // range may only be in the positive sign domain
3338 {
3339 while (it != itEnd) {
3340 if (!qIsNaN(it->mainValue())) {
3341 current = it->mainKey();
3342 if ((current < range.lower || !haveLower) && current > 0) {
3343 range.lower = current;
3344 haveLower = true;
3345 }
3346 if ((current > range.upper || !haveUpper) && current > 0) {
3347 range.upper = current;
3348 haveUpper = true;
3349 }
3350 }
3351 ++it;
3352 }
3353 }
3354
3355 foundRange = haveLower && haveUpper;
3356 return range;
3357}
3358
3375template <class DataType>
3376QCPRange QCPDataContainer<DataType>::valueRange(bool &foundRange, QCP::SignDomain signDomain,
3377 const QCPRange &inKeyRange) {
3378 if (isEmpty()) {
3379 foundRange = false;
3380 return QCPRange();
3381 }
3382 QCPRange range;
3383 const bool restrictKeyRange = inKeyRange != QCPRange();
3384 bool haveLower = false;
3385 bool haveUpper = false;
3386 QCPRange current;
3387 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator itBegin = constBegin();
3388 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator itEnd = constEnd();
3389 if (DataType::sortKeyIsMainKey() && restrictKeyRange) {
3390 itBegin = findBegin(inKeyRange.lower, false);
3391 itEnd = findEnd(inKeyRange.upper, false);
3392 }
3393 if (signDomain == QCP::sdBoth) // range may be anywhere
3394 {
3395 for (QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator it = itBegin; it != itEnd; ++it) {
3396 if (restrictKeyRange && (it->mainKey() < inKeyRange.lower || it->mainKey() > inKeyRange.upper))
3397 continue;
3398 current = it->valueRange();
3399 if ((current.lower < range.lower || !haveLower) && !qIsNaN(current.lower)) {
3400 range.lower = current.lower;
3401 haveLower = true;
3402 }
3403 if ((current.upper > range.upper || !haveUpper) && !qIsNaN(current.upper)) {
3404 range.upper = current.upper;
3405 haveUpper = true;
3406 }
3407 }
3408 } else if (signDomain == QCP::sdNegative) // range may only be in the negative sign domain
3409 {
3410 for (QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator it = itBegin; it != itEnd; ++it) {
3411 if (restrictKeyRange && (it->mainKey() < inKeyRange.lower || it->mainKey() > inKeyRange.upper))
3412 continue;
3413 current = it->valueRange();
3414 if ((current.lower < range.lower || !haveLower) && current.lower < 0 && !qIsNaN(current.lower)) {
3415 range.lower = current.lower;
3416 haveLower = true;
3417 }
3418 if ((current.upper > range.upper || !haveUpper) && current.upper < 0 && !qIsNaN(current.upper)) {
3419 range.upper = current.upper;
3420 haveUpper = true;
3421 }
3422 }
3423 } else if (signDomain == QCP::sdPositive) // range may only be in the positive sign domain
3424 {
3425 for (QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator it = itBegin; it != itEnd; ++it) {
3426 if (restrictKeyRange && (it->mainKey() < inKeyRange.lower || it->mainKey() > inKeyRange.upper))
3427 continue;
3428 current = it->valueRange();
3429 if ((current.lower < range.lower || !haveLower) && current.lower > 0 && !qIsNaN(current.lower)) {
3430 range.lower = current.lower;
3431 haveLower = true;
3432 }
3433 if ((current.upper > range.upper || !haveUpper) && current.upper > 0 && !qIsNaN(current.upper)) {
3434 range.upper = current.upper;
3435 haveUpper = true;
3436 }
3437 }
3438 }
3439
3440 foundRange = haveLower && haveUpper;
3441 return range;
3442}
3443
3452template <class DataType>
3453void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::limitIteratorsToDataRange(const_iterator &begin, const_iterator &end,
3454 const QCPDataRange &dataRange) const {
3455 QCPDataRange iteratorRange(int(begin - constBegin()), int(end - constBegin()));
3456 iteratorRange = iteratorRange.bounded(dataRange.bounded(this->dataRange()));
3457 begin = constBegin() + iteratorRange.begin();
3458 end = constBegin() + iteratorRange.end();
3459}
3460
3470template <class DataType>
3471void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::preallocateGrow(int minimumPreallocSize) {
3472 if (minimumPreallocSize <= mPreallocSize) return;
3473
3474 int newPreallocSize = minimumPreallocSize;
3475 newPreallocSize += (1u << qBound(4, mPreallocIteration + 4, 15)) -
3476 12; // do 4 up to 32768-12 preallocation, doubling in each intermediate iteration
3477 ++mPreallocIteration;
3478
3479 int sizeDifference = newPreallocSize - mPreallocSize;
3480 mData.resize(mData.size() + sizeDifference);
3481 std::copy_backward(mData.begin() + mPreallocSize, mData.end() - sizeDifference, mData.end());
3482 mPreallocSize = newPreallocSize;
3483}
3484
3499template <class DataType>
3500void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::performAutoSqueeze() {
3501 const int totalAlloc = mData.capacity();
3502 const int postAllocSize = totalAlloc - mData.size();
3503 const int usedSize = size();
3504 bool shrinkPostAllocation = false;
3505 bool shrinkPreAllocation = false;
3506 if (totalAlloc > 650000) // if allocation is larger, shrink earlier with respect to total used size
3507 {
3508 shrinkPostAllocation =
3509 postAllocSize >
3510 usedSize * 1.5; // QVector grow strategy is 2^n for static data. Watch out not to oscillate!
3511 shrinkPreAllocation = mPreallocSize * 10 > usedSize;
3512 } else if (totalAlloc > 1000) // below 10 MiB raw data be generous with preallocated memory, below 1k
3513 // points don't even bother
3514 {
3515 shrinkPostAllocation = postAllocSize > usedSize * 5;
3516 shrinkPreAllocation =
3517 mPreallocSize > usedSize * 1.5; // preallocation can grow into postallocation, so can be smaller
3518 }
3519
3520 if (shrinkPreAllocation || shrinkPostAllocation) squeeze(shrinkPreAllocation, shrinkPostAllocation);
3521}

4174// implementation of template functions:
4175
4194template <class PlottableType>
4195PlottableType *QCustomPlot::plottableAt(const QPointF &pos, bool onlySelectable, int *dataIndex) const {
4196 PlottableType *resultPlottable = 0;
4197 QVariant resultDetails;
4198 double resultDistance =
4199 mSelectionTolerance; // only regard clicks with distances smaller than mSelectionTolerance as
4200 // selections, so initialize with that value
4201
4202 foreach (QCPAbstractPlottable *plottable, mPlottables) {
4203 PlottableType *currentPlottable = qobject_cast<PlottableType *>(plottable);
4204 if (!currentPlottable ||
4205 (onlySelectable &&
4206 !currentPlottable->selectable())) // we could have also passed onlySelectable to the selectTest
4207 // function, but checking here is faster, because we have
4208 // access to QCPAbstractPlottable::selectable
4209 continue;
4210 if (currentPlottable->clipRect().contains(
4211 pos.toPoint())) // only consider clicks where the plottable is actually visible
4212 {
4213 QVariant details;
4214 double currentDistance =
4215 currentPlottable->selectTest(pos, false, dataIndex ? &details : nullptr);
4216 if (currentDistance >= 0 && currentDistance < resultDistance) {
4217 resultPlottable = currentPlottable;
4218 resultDetails = details;
4219 resultDistance = currentDistance;
4220 }
4221 }
4222 }
4223
4224 if (resultPlottable && dataIndex) {
4225 QCPDataSelection sel = resultDetails.value<QCPDataSelection>();
4226 if (!sel.isEmpty()) *dataIndex = sel.dataRange(0).begin();
4227 }
4228 return resultPlottable;
4229}
4230
4244template <class ItemType>
4245ItemType *QCustomPlot::itemAt(const QPointF &pos, bool onlySelectable) const {
4246 ItemType *resultItem = 0;
4247 double resultDistance =
4248 mSelectionTolerance; // only regard clicks with distances smaller than mSelectionTolerance as
4249 // selections, so initialize with that value
4250
4251 foreach (QCPAbstractItem *item, mItems) {
4252 ItemType *currentItem = qobject_cast<ItemType *>(item);
4253 if (!currentItem ||
4254 (onlySelectable &&
4255 !currentItem->selectable())) // we could have also passed onlySelectable to the selectTest
4256 // function, but checking here is faster, because we have access
4257 // to QCPAbstractItem::selectable
4258 continue;
4259 if (!currentItem->clipToAxisRect() ||
4260 currentItem->clipRect().contains(pos.toPoint())) // only consider clicks inside axis cliprect of
4261 // the item if actually clipped to it
4262 {
4263 double currentDistance = currentItem->selectTest(pos, false);
4264 if (currentDistance >= 0 && currentDistance < resultDistance) {
4265 resultItem = currentItem;
4266 resultDistance = currentDistance;
4267 }
4268 }
4269 }
4270
4271 return resultItem;
4272}

4610
4618template <class DataType>
4619QCPDataSelection QCPAbstractPlottable1D<DataType>::selectTestRect(const QRectF &rect,
4620 bool onlySelectable) const {
4621 QCPDataSelection result;
4622 if ((onlySelectable && mSelectable == QCP::stNone) || mDataContainer->isEmpty()) return result;
4623 if (!mKeyAxis || !mValueAxis) return result;
4624
4625 // convert rect given in pixels to ranges given in plot coordinates:
4626 double key1, value1, key2, value2;
4627 pixelsToCoords(rect.topLeft(), key1, value1);
4628 pixelsToCoords(rect.bottomRight(), key2, value2);
4629 QCPRange keyRange(
4630 key1, key2); // QCPRange normalizes internally so we don't have to care about whether key1 < key2
4631 QCPRange valueRange(value1, value2);
4632 typename QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator begin = mDataContainer->constBegin();
4633 typename QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator end = mDataContainer->constEnd();
4634 if (DataType::sortKeyIsMainKey()) // we can assume that data is sorted by main key, so can reduce the
4635 // searched key interval:
4636 {
4637 begin = mDataContainer->findBegin(keyRange.lower, false);
4638 end = mDataContainer->findEnd(keyRange.upper, false);
4639 }
4640 if (begin == end) return result;
4641
4642 int currentSegmentBegin = -1; // -1 means we're currently not in a segment that's contained in rect
4643 for (typename QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator it = begin; it != end; ++it) {
4644 if (currentSegmentBegin == -1) {
4645 if (valueRange.contains(it->mainValue()) && keyRange.contains(it->mainKey())) // start segment
4646 currentSegmentBegin = int(it - mDataContainer->constBegin());
4647 } else if (!valueRange.contains(it->mainValue()) ||
4648 !keyRange.contains(it->mainKey())) // segment just ended
4649 {
4650 result.addDataRange(QCPDataRange(currentSegmentBegin, int(it - mDataContainer->constBegin())),
4651 false);
4652 currentSegmentBegin = -1;
4653 }
4654 }
4655 // process potential last segment:
4656 if (currentSegmentBegin != -1)
4657 result.addDataRange(QCPDataRange(currentSegmentBegin, int(end - mDataContainer->constBegin())),
4658 false);
4659
4660 result.simplify();
4661 return result;
4662}
4663
4667template <class DataType>
4668int QCPAbstractPlottable1D<DataType>::findBegin(double sortKey, bool expandedRange) const {
4669 return int(mDataContainer->findBegin(sortKey, expandedRange) - mDataContainer->constBegin());
4670}
4671
4675template <class DataType>
4676int QCPAbstractPlottable1D<DataType>::findEnd(double sortKey, bool expandedRange) const {
4677 return int(mDataContainer->findEnd(sortKey, expandedRange) - mDataContainer->constBegin());
4678}
4679
4690template <class DataType>
4691double QCPAbstractPlottable1D<DataType>::selectTest(const QPointF &pos, bool onlySelectable,
4692 QVariant *details) const {
4693 if ((onlySelectable && mSelectable == QCP::stNone) || mDataContainer->isEmpty()) return -1;
4694 if (!mKeyAxis || !mValueAxis) return -1;
4695
4696 QCPDataSelection selectionResult;
4697 double minDistSqr = (std::numeric_limits<double>::max)();
4698 int minDistIndex = mDataContainer->size();
4699
4700 typename QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator begin = mDataContainer->constBegin();
4701 typename QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator end = mDataContainer->constEnd();
4702 if (DataType::sortKeyIsMainKey()) // we can assume that data is sorted by main key, so can reduce the
4703 // searched key interval:
4704 {
4705 // determine which key range comes into question, taking selection tolerance around pos into account:
4706 double posKeyMin, posKeyMax, dummy;
4707 pixelsToCoords(pos - QPointF(mParentPlot->selectionTolerance(), mParentPlot->selectionTolerance()),
4708 posKeyMin, dummy);
4709 pixelsToCoords(pos + QPointF(mParentPlot->selectionTolerance(), mParentPlot->selectionTolerance()),
4710 posKeyMax, dummy);
4711 if (posKeyMin > posKeyMax) qSwap(posKeyMin, posKeyMax);
4712 begin = mDataContainer->findBegin(posKeyMin, true);
4713 end = mDataContainer->findEnd(posKeyMax, true);
4714 }
4715 if (begin == end) return -1;
4716 QCPRange keyRange(mKeyAxis->range());
4717 QCPRange valueRange(mValueAxis->range());
4718 for (typename QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator it = begin; it != end; ++it) {
4719 const double mainKey = it->mainKey();
4720 const double mainValue = it->mainValue();
4721 if (keyRange.contains(mainKey) &&
4722 valueRange.contains(
4723 mainValue)) // make sure data point is inside visible range, for speedup in cases where sort
4724 // key isn't main key and we iterate over all points
4725 {
4726 const double currentDistSqr =
4727 QCPVector2D(coordsToPixels(mainKey, mainValue) - pos).lengthSquared();
4728 if (currentDistSqr < minDistSqr) {
4729 minDistSqr = currentDistSqr;
4730 minDistIndex = int(it - mDataContainer->constBegin());
4731 }
4732 }
4733 }
4734 if (minDistIndex != mDataContainer->size())
4735 selectionResult.addDataRange(QCPDataRange(minDistIndex, minDistIndex + 1), false);
4736
4737 selectionResult.simplify();
4738 if (details) details->setValue(selectionResult);
4739 return qSqrt(minDistSqr);
4740}
4741
4752template <class DataType>
4753void QCPAbstractPlottable1D<DataType>::getDataSegments(QList<QCPDataRange> &selectedSegments,
4754 QList<QCPDataRange> &unselectedSegments) const {
4755 selectedSegments.clear();
4756 unselectedSegments.clear();
4757 if (mSelectable == QCP::stWhole) // stWhole selection type draws the entire plottable with selected
4758 // style if mSelection isn't empty
4759 {
4760 if (selected())
4761 selectedSegments << QCPDataRange(0, dataCount());
4762 else
4763 unselectedSegments << QCPDataRange(0, dataCount());
4764 } else {
4765 QCPDataSelection sel(selection());
4766 sel.simplify();
4767 selectedSegments = sel.dataRanges();
4768 unselectedSegments = sel.inverse(QCPDataRange(0, dataCount())).dataRanges();
4769 }
4770}
4771
4782template <class DataType>
4783void QCPAbstractPlottable1D<DataType>::drawPolyline(QCPPainter *painter,
4784 const QVector<QPointF> &lineData) const {
4785 // if drawing lines in plot (instead of PDF), reduce 1px lines to cosmetic, because at least in
4786 // Qt6 drawing of "1px" width lines is much slower even though it has same appearance apart from
4787 // High-DPI. In High-DPI cases people must set a pen width slightly larger than 1.0 to get
4788 // correct DPI scaling of width, but of course with performance penalty.
4789 if (!painter->modes().testFlag(QCPPainter::pmVectorized) &&
4790 qFuzzyCompare(painter->pen().widthF(), 1.0)) {
4791 QPen newPen = painter->pen();
4792 newPen.setWidth(0);
4793 painter->setPen(newPen);
4794 }
4795
4796 // if drawing solid line and not in PDF, use much faster line drawing instead of polyline:
4797 if (mParentPlot->plottingHints().testFlag(QCP::phFastPolylines) &&
4798 painter->pen().style() == Qt::SolidLine && !painter->modes().testFlag(QCPPainter::pmVectorized) &&
4799 !painter->modes().testFlag(QCPPainter::pmNoCaching)) {
4800 int i = 0;
4801 bool lastIsNan = false;
4802 const int lineDataSize = lineData.size();
4803 while (i < lineDataSize && (qIsNaN(lineData.at(i).y()) ||
4804 qIsNaN(lineData.at(i).x()))) // make sure first point is not NaN
4805 ++i;
4806 ++i; // because drawing works in 1 point retrospect
4807 while (i < lineDataSize) {
4808 if (!qIsNaN(lineData.at(i).y()) && !qIsNaN(lineData.at(i).x())) // NaNs create a gap in the line
4809 {
4810 if (!lastIsNan)
4811 painter->drawLine(lineData.at(i - 1), lineData.at(i));
4812 else
4813 lastIsNan = false;
4814 } else
4815 lastIsNan = true;
4816 ++i;
4817 }
4818 } else {
4819 int segmentStart = 0;
4820 int i = 0;
4821 const int lineDataSize = lineData.size();
4822 while (i < lineDataSize) {
4823 if (qIsNaN(lineData.at(i).y()) || qIsNaN(lineData.at(i).x()) ||
4824 qIsInf(lineData.at(i).y())) // NaNs create a gap in the line. Also filter Infs which make
4825 // drawPolyline block
4826 {
4827 painter->drawPolyline(
4828 lineData.constData() + segmentStart,
4829 i - segmentStart); // i, because we don't want to include the current NaN point
4830 segmentStart = i + 1;
4831 }
4832 ++i;
4833 }
4834 // draw last segment:
4835 painter->drawPolyline(lineData.constData() + segmentStart, lineDataSize - segmentStart);
4836 }
4837}

6069class QCP_LIB_DECL QCPStatisticalBoxData {
6070 public:
6071 QCPStatisticalBoxData();
6072 QCPStatisticalBoxData(double key, double minimum, double lowerQuartile, double median,
6073 double upperQuartile, double maximum,
6074 const QVector<double> &outliers = QVector<double>());
6075
6076 inline double sortKey() const { return key; }
6077 inline static QCPStatisticalBoxData fromSortKey(double sortKey) {
6078 return QCPStatisticalBoxData(sortKey, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
6079 }
6080 inline static bool sortKeyIsMainKey() { return true; }
6081
6082 inline double mainKey() const { return key; }
6083 inline double mainValue() const { return median; }
6084
6085 inline QCPRange valueRange() const {
6086 QCPRange result(minimum, maximum);
6087 for (QVector<double>::const_iterator it = outliers.constBegin(); it != outliers.constEnd(); ++it)
6088 result.expand(*it);
6089 return result;
6090 }
6091
6092 double key, minimum, lowerQuartile, median, upperQuartile, maximum;
6093 QVector<double> outliers;
6094};

7646 double coordToAngleRad(double coord) const {
7647 return mAngleRad +
7648 (coord - mRange.lower) / mRange.size() * (mRangeReversed ? -2.0 * M_PI : 2.0 * M_PI);
7649 } // mention in doc that return doesn't wrap
7650 double angleRadToCoord(double angleRad) const {
7651 return mRange.lower +
7652 (angleRad - mAngleRad) / (mRangeReversed ? -2.0 * M_PI : 2.0 * M_PI) * mRange.size();
7653 }
